longBusinessSummary: Massmart Holdings Limited operates as a retail and wholesale distributor. It operates through four divisions: Massdiscounters, Masswarehouse, Massbuild, and Masscash. The Massdiscounters division operates discount retail stores that offer general merchandise, fresh food, groceries, and liquor, as well as technological solutions in multimedia and hi-tech under the Game and DionWired retail formats. This division operates 173 stores in South Africa, Botswana, Ghana, Kenya, Lesotho, Malawi, Mozambique, Namibia, Nigeria, Tanzania, Uganda, and Zambia. The Masswarehouse division operates warehouse stores under the Makro and The Fruitspot names that sell food, liquor, and general merchandise for retail, commercial, and wholesale customers; and fresh and cut fruit and vegetables, as well as provides crowd-sourced final mile delivery services to individuals and corporates. This division operates 22 stores in South Africa. The Massbuild division operates DIY, home improvement, and building materials stores under the Builders Warehouse, Builders Express, Builders Superstore, and Builders Trade Depot brands. This division operates 118 stores in South Africa, Botswana, Mozambique, and Zambia. The Masscash division engages in the wholesale of food and cosmetic products under the CBW, Trident, Jumbo Cash & Carry, Sunshine, Eureka, Saverite, and Shield brands; and operation of retail outlets under the Cambridge Food and Rhino brands. This division operates 130 stores South Africa, Botswana, Lesotho, Mozambique, Namibia, Swaziland, and Zambia. It also engages in the management, investment, and finance businesses; and property holding business. The company was founded in 1990 and is headquartered in Sandton, South Africa. Massmart Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Main Street 830 Proprietary Limited.
